<doc id="1105955" wikidata="Q393561" url="?curid=1105955" title="Agia Eirini, Cephalonia">
<text>Agia Eirini (, for Saint Irene) is a community in the municipal unit of Eleios-Pronnoi in the southeastern part of the island of Cephalonia, Greece. It is situated in an inland valley, at about 90 m elevation. It is 2 km south of Tzanata, 3 km southeast of Xenopoulo, 3 km north of Pastra and 4 km southwest of Poros. It is located on the road connecting Poros with Argostoli.

==Historical population==

