A consequence is that the cyclotomic polynomials are self-reciprocal for . This is used in the special number field sieve to allow numbers of the form and to be factored taking advantage of the algebraic factors by using polynomials of degree 5, 6, 4 and 6 respectively – note that (Euler&#x27;s totient function) of the exponents are 10, 12, 8 and 12.

Per Cohn&#x27;s theorem, a self-inversive polynomial has as many roots in the unit disk formula_14 as the reciprocal polynomial of its derivative.

